      "content": "That makes sense from a purely operational standpoint. But looking at the broader market trends, when we talk about \"demographic shifts\" in these types of urban zones, it usually refers to a change in the racial and ethnic makeup of the neighborhood. In your professional assessment, how do those specific types of changes impact the long-term valuation and perceived safety of an investment compared to a more homogenous, established area?",
